thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: [BG] Some mammals have teeth. Platypus have no teeth. Platypus are mammals. Humans have teeth.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Platypus are reptiles.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
Teeth(x) ::: x has teeth.
Reptile(x) ::: x is a reptile.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Premises:
∃x (Mammal(x) ∧ Teeth(x)) ::: Some mammals have teeth.
Mammal(platypus) ∧ ¬Teeth(platypus) ::: Platypus are mammals and have no teeth.
Human(humans) ∧ Teeth(humans) ::: Humans have teeth.
Conclusion:
Reptile(platypus) ::: Platypus are reptiles.
